	(text_box "PICO\n\nOne PIO will wait on ~{IORW} and when triggered place data in RX FIFO. DMA will move this into memory of CPU to decode and place in memory associated with IO Address.\n\nOne PIO will wait on ~{CSRD} and when triggered place data in TX FIFO. DMA will provide data into PIO. Not figured this bit out yet fully. "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 454.66 15.24 0)
		(size 123.19 107.95)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "4bdba54b-e7db-4fbe-8239-e31e04b28daf")
	)
	(text_box "CONTROL (CTRL)\n\nThis transceiver buffers the control signals associated with IO Reads and Writes from the CPC.\n\nChip Select Read (~{CSRD}) is active low when CPC is reading the Pico simulated IO port i.e. F8E0. The Pico will use this as a trigger to place the next data byte on the data lines and change direction of the Data Transciever.\n\nA0 and A1 have also been provided as an optional address selection and may allocate these to return the CRTC, GA or PIO data but not decided yet.\n\n~{IOWR} active is low when the CPC is executing any IO Write, which will include the CRTC, GA or PIO. The PICO will use this as a trigger to log the data.\n\nCTRL Chip Enable (~{CTRL_CE}) will be pulled low by the PICO when powered."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 309.88 24.13 0)
		(size 140.97 93.98)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "78841e28-a9c4-4ad5-89aa-504c7dd4f682")
	)
	(text_box "Address High Byte (ADHB)\n\nThis transceiver buffers the high byte of the IO Write from the CPC. Only the High Byte of the Address is used on the Amstrad CPC to select the CRTC, GA and PIO.\n\nNote on the Amstrad CPC selection of the CRTC, GA and PIO is made with a single active low address line (i.e. B14 low selects the CRTC)\n\nAddress High Byte Chip Enable (~{ADHB_CE}) will be pulled low by the PICO when powered."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 309.88 121.92 0)
		(size 140.97 147.32)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "83a69226-a17d-44c1-b480-2e4724997dfa")
	)
	(text_box "DATA\n\nThis transceiver buffers the high byte of the Data lines to and from the CPC. \n\nThe direction of data will be controlled by the Pico using Data Chip Enable (DATA_AB). By default this will be A to B and only on a IO Port Read will the Pico change this to B to A.\n\nData Chip Enable (~{DATA_CE}) will be pulled low by the PICO when powered."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 309.88 273.05 0)
		(size 140.97 116.84)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "9e90cfa7-ba4a-4a2b-8800-7d8ed4f2e18d")
	)
	(text_box "POWER DECOUPLING"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 16.51 264.16 0)
		(size 170.18 58.42)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
